import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    zip_count = data['state'].value_counts()
    ax = sns.barplot(x=zip_count.index, y=zip_count.values)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Zip Codes')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
